I need a few things sorted out before we make the switch.
1. do we still provide security updates to v3.1. If so, we must release the CA bundle for that version as well.
2. can we get a test host cert to do a quick test on the format of the intermediate ca file? We are not going to do any extensive tetsing, we did that 2 years ago. Bt I want to do a quick sanity test on if there is any obvious problems with the new intermediate ca.
3. Most importantly we need to alert our users that they need to instal this new intermediate CA to their browser trust store. We need some time to make the announcement and give everyone a chance to respond.

Mine</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='22049#1438633992'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-08-03T20:33:12+00:00">Aug 3, 2015 08:33 PM UTC</time> by <b>OSG RA</b><a class="anchor" name="1438633992">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Security,

