The user certificates issued from the DigiCert Pilot account are now being issued from the SHA2 &#34;DigiCert Grid TEST CA-1 G2&#34; CA. Please test that the certificate issuance is working in your test environment.

What we are working towards is twofold.
1. All of your end entity Grid certificates are being issued as SHA2 (disable the ability to request a SHA1 cert)
2. The intermediate CA certificate that the certificates are issued from is also SHA2 (DigiCert Grid Test CA-1 G2)

Once you are done on the test (pilot) account we would like to push the following changes to your production account.
1. Disable the ability for you to issue SHA1 certificates
2. Switch the intermediate CA that signs your certificates to the SHA2 production Grid intermediate named &#34;DigiCert Grid CA-1 G2&#34;.

DigiCert is ready and waiting for the approval from OSG to push the changes to your production account. If DigiCert can receive approval to push the changes for SHA2 compliance live on your production account on Tuesday the 25th of November 2014 that would be best for IGTF compliance. If you are not ready at that time we can shoot for Tuesday the 9th of December 2014.

Thank you,

Darin Andrew, CISSP
Technical Engineer
DigiCert, Inc.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='22049#1416504484'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-11-20T17:28:04+00:00">Nov 20, 2014 05:28 PM UTC</time> by <b>Soichi Hayashi</b><a class="anchor" name="1416504484">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Darin,

