We have created the new SHA2 intermediate which chains up to the DigiCert Grid TEST Root CA. The new intermediate is named &#34;DigiCert Grid TEST CA-1 G2&#34;.

As of 5&#58;29pm MT today (10/21/2014), the OSG test account (account number 052062) has been setup to only allow SHA2 certificates to be issued. The SHA2 certificates will all be issued from the new SHA2 intermediate as well. This will allow you to test your code to not allow SHA1 certificates from being issued and to ensure the new SHA2 test intermediate will not cause issues.

This change was only made to the test account. No changes have been made to your production account. The plan now is that DigiCert will wait for you to test this change to your test account. Once you have completed your testing you will give us the go ahead to make the switch to your production account. Along with your approval to apply the change to the production account please provide the exact date when you want DigiCert to apply the change to the production account.

Thank you,

Darin Andrew, CISSP
Technical Engineer
DigiCert, Inc.
